{{Quote|I worked for a short time with Vulca Minerals when they were still dealing with Guiteica. After Vulca got a little too pushy about yttrium mining, the Order just about killed the Team Commander on the spot.|[[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenant]] [[Ayla Shar]], in a [[Task Force on Alliance Security]] [[SecuriDex]] [[Datafile/Legends|datafile]] on the m'Yalfor'ac Order|<ref name="AIR" />}}
'''Yttrium''' was a rare<ref name="LoNH" /> [[Mineral/Legends|mineral]].<ref name="AIR" /> It was among the several different [[Ore/Legends|ores]] and minerals that, by the time of the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] between the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]], were being extracted from the crust of the [[Stone/Legends|rocky]]<ref name="LoNH" /> [[Hutt Space/Legends|Hutt Space]]<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Nar Kreeta]].<ref name="LoNH" />

Extensive subterranean deposits of yttrium were also located on [[Guiteica/Legends|Guiteica]], a planet<ref name="AIR" /> in [[Wild Space/Legends|Wild Space's]] [[Kadok Regions/Legends|Kadok Regions]].<ref name="EAOC">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-atlas-online-companion|text=''Star Wars: The Essential Atlas'' Online Companion|int=Star Wars: The Essential Atlas Online Companion}} &mdash; Based on corresponding data for [[Tertiary Kadok system]]</ref> At some point by [[2 ABY/Legends|2 ABY]],<ref name="Date">''[[Alliance Intelligence Reports]]'' represents a collection of [[in-universe]] reports from "one [[Standard year/Legends|year]] before the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]]," which corresponds to [[2 ABY/Legends|2 ABY]], according to ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''.</ref> when the [[Vulca Minerals]] company attempted to aggressively negotiate with Guiteica's [[Homeworld/Legends|native]] [[Bitthævrian/Legends|Bitthævrian]] [[Species/Legends|species]] the rights to [[Mining/Legends|mine]] yttrium, the [[m'Yalfor'ac Order]], the dominant Bitthævrian continental [[Army/Legends|army]], nearly [[Death/Legends|killed]] the company's [[Team Commander]]. Since that incident, all of Guiteica's exports were managed by the company [[Kadok Resources]].<ref name="AIR" />

==Behind the scenes==
Yttrium was first introduced to the ''[[Star Wars]]'' franchise in ''[[Alliance Intelligence Reports]]'', a [[1995]] sourcebook for [[West End Games]]' ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]''.<ref name="AIR" /> In the real world, [[Wikipedia:Yttrium|yttrium]] is a [[Wikipedia:Chemical element|chemical element]] and [[Wikipedia:Rare-earth element|rare-earth metal]] that is primarily extracted from [[Wikipedia:Rare-earth mineral|rare-earth ores]] and has a wide range of industrial applications.<ref name="YttriumBritannica">{{WebCite|url=https://www.britannica.com/science/yttrium|text=Yttrium &#124; Chemical Element, Uses in Electronics, & Medicine|author=The Editors of Encyclopædia Britannica|date=2024-03-04|work=[[Wikipedia:Encyclopædia Britannica|''Encyclopædia Britannica'']]|archivedate=20250220080354}}</ref>

